The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Two killed in mishaps
                                                                                                               Two killed in mishaps
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	An elderly morning walker and a young home guard were killed in separate road mishaps in the city on Thursday.        
	Amit Kumar Kundu, 58, was hit by a private bus on route 91C near the No. 15 bus stand on Ultadanga Main Road around 8.55am. He was on his way home after his morning work in a nearby park via the local market.         
	The rear wheels of the bus crushed Kundus head, said an officer of Maniktala police station. The driver jumped off the vehicle and ran away. The bus was impounded.        
	Residents of the area took him to RG Kar Medical College and Hospital, where he was declared dead on arrival.         
	Around 1.30pm, Prabir Kumar Gupta, a 20-year-old home guard of Jorabagan traffic guard, was knocked down on Strand Road by a CSTC bus plying on route 7A.        
	Gupta, who was on duty, was recruited before the general elections. He was pronounced dead at Medical College and Hospital.        
	The youth, a resident of Uttarpara, is survived by his elderly parents. The driver, who allegedly didnt slam the brakes even after seeing Gupta crossing the road, was arrested.                                                                                                                                                                            
